lcers and bleeding.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03782,0.072932,0.082358,0.089351,0.094864,0.10057,0.098096,0.096016,0.091006,0.090083,0.078978,0.067927],"unified_progress":[0.069771,0.092201,0.086544,0.085329,0.087198,0.090309,0.088798,0.090946,0.086423,0.083474,0.075937,0.06307]},{"section":16,"text":"The other meds: atenolol is a beta-blocker, which might not directly cause bleeding, but nitrates also are part of his regimen.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039551,0.077269,0.087798,0.093535,0.096459,0.09981,0.097974,0.094762,0.089902,0.085501,0.075727,0.061712],"unified_progress":[0.063624,0.093323,0.095747,0.09621,0.096673,0.096252,0.092445,0.089755,0.082959,0.076099,0.065885,0.051029]},{"section":17,"text":"Other possibilities?","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031761,0.071237,0.092393,0.098895,0.099119,0.09454,0.093993,0.091125,0.088424,0.090347,0.077892,0.070273],"unified_progress":[0.038218,0.075024,0.087117,0.10236,0.099731,0.095573,0.097104,0.092761,0.08821,0.092323,0.074423,0.057153]},{"section":18,"text":"Maybe aortic dissection, but that usually has severe chest pain and other signs.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021706,0.055476,0.071195,0.082008,0.090694,0.096292,0.1056,0.10755,0.10544,0.10214,0.094158,0.067737],"unified_progress":[0.028038,0.057431,0.074318,0.082676,0.095254,0.098257,0.1018,0.10765,0.10571,0.10732,0.086245,0.055303]},{"section":19,"text":"Hemorrhagic stroke?","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026821,0.061529,0.074246,0.084176,0.092529,0.098552,0.10275,0.10288,0.1015,0.09675,0.087413,0.07085],"unified_progress":[0.031993,0.060793,0.076053,0.086973,0.0943,0.10078,0.10163,0.10286,0.10208,0.097474,0.083937,0.061132]},{"section":20,"text":"But the fall could be due to syncope from hypotension.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025738,0.058051,0.06946,0.079922,0.090393,0.098698,0.10468,0.10416,0.10184,0.097118,0.091976,0.077955],"unified_progress":[0.035199,0.051088,0.062563,0.071293,0.083637,0.096007,0.097709,0.10328,0.10698,0.10789,0.10237,0.081992]},{"section":21,"text":"The black stool points more to GI bleed.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026911,0.060873,0.075437,0.084977,0.09075,0.094568,0.099053,0.098517,0.099664,0.097561,0.090595,0.081092],"unified_progress":[0.036877,0.054689,0.067748,0.078618,0.087846,0.093909,0.097452,0.10012,0.10304,0.10447,0.096286,0.078946]},{"section":22,"text":"So the most likely diagnosis is upper gastrointestinal bleeding, likely from a peptic ulcer caused or worsened by aspirin.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025536,0.054342,0.065626,0.074672,0.082125,0.088368,0.093294,0.094484,0.098264,0.097565,0.10001,0.12571],"unified_progress":[0.027802,0.043619,0.055022,0.065277,0.072497,0.083139,0.08668,0.09447,0.10263,0.10583,0.12239,0.14065]},{"section":23,"text":"The hypotension and tachycardia are the body's response to blood loss.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023204,0.052698,0.06502,0.076401,0.087444,0.095861,0.10355,0.10363,0.10323,0.10064,0.098842,0.089475],"unified_progress":[0.034961,0.042538,0.052733,0.061849,0.074788,0.088667,0.09338,0.1024,0.11175,0.11808,0.11889,0.099957]},{"section":24,"text":"I don't think it's a ruptured aneurysm or something else because the history and meds point more towards GI.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028128,0.06151,0.073985,0.0823,0.087832,0.092689,0.097419,0.099121,0.10093,0.098928,0.092467,0.084688],"unified_progress":[0.032525,0.056163,0.068656,0.078733,0.086233,0.091526,0.095757,0.099995,0.10296,0.10557,0.098769,0.083115]},{"section":25,"text":"So the answer should be upper GI bleed, probably peptic ulcer bleed.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.